  <div class="prose">
    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>When you join Krenla, you pick a handful of topics you care about. That's your starting signal. As you interact — joining communities, upvoting threads, spending time in certain rooms — the feed gets more accurate. It learns what you engage with meaningfully, not just what you click.</p>

    <p>We don't use engagement bait signals like outrage or controversy to keep you on the platform longer. Discovery is tuned for satisfaction, not session length.</p>

    <h2>What surfaces in your feed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Trending threads</strong> from communities in your interest areas</li>
      <li><strong>Community recommendations</strong> based on what similar members have joined</li>
      <li><strong>New communities</strong> in topics you follow, surfaced when they hit early traction</li>
      <li><strong>Highlighted conversations</strong> from communities you're already in</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Control your feed</h2>
    <p>You can tune discovery at any time from your settings. Add or remove topics, mute specific communities from appearing, or reset your signal entirely. You're not locked into the algorithm's early read on you.</p>

    <div class="note">
      Discovery is opt-in. If you'd rather not have a personalized feed, you can use a topic-based browse mode instead — no personalization, just content sorted by recent activity.
    </div>

    <h2>For community owners</h2>
    <p>Krenla doesn't sell placement in discovery. Communities surface based on activity, member growth, and content quality signals — not ad spend. A community with 200 passionate members posting great threads will appear alongside much larger ones.</p>
  </div>
</Page>
